===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# One who, or that which, [[shifts]] or [[changes]].
# {{lb|en|linguistics}} A [[word]] whose [[meaning]] changes depending on the situation, as by [[deixis]].
# {{label|en|dated}} One who plays [[tricks]] or practices [[artifice]]; a [[cozener]].
#: ''&apos;Twas such a '''shifter''' that, if truth were known, Death was half glad when he had got him down.'' &mdash; Milton.
# {{label|en|nautical}} An [[assistant]] to the [[ship]]'s [[cook]] in washing, steeping, and shifting the salt provisions.
# {{label|en|engineering}} An arrangement for shifting a [[belt]] [[sidewise]] from one [[pulley]] to another.
# {{label|en|engineering|textiles}} A [[wire]] for changing a [[loop]] from one [[needle]] to another, as in [[narrow]]ing, etc.
# {{label|en|cycling}} A [[component]] used by the [[rider]] to control the gearing mechanisms and select the desired [[gear ratio]], usually connected to the [[derailleur]] by a [[mechanical]] [[actuation]] [[cable]].
# A [[spanner]] with an adjustable jaw size.
# {{label|en|mythology|science fiction|fantasy}} A [[shape-shifter]], or a person or other being capable of changing their physical form.
# {{label|en|erotica}} A genre of [[erotica]] focusing on [[lycanthrope]]s or other [[shapeshifter]]s, such as [[werewolves]].

